<h3>Expedience</h3>
<p>This spell increases the movement speed of your pet by 20%.&nbsp; That's
better than Journeyman Boots!&nbsp; Your pet will be able to keep up with you
better and chase down its targets faster when this spell is on it.&nbsp; You may
have noticed that if your pet is chasing a moving mob, it has trouble keeping up
since it will stop to cast a spell frequently.&nbsp; Expedience comes in
handy!&nbsp; Like most movement rate spells, this spell can only be cast
outdoors.&nbsp; (Why?&nbsp; Mages aren't druids, using the strength of
nature....)</p>

<h3>Sword of Runes</h3>
<p>This sword is the only summoned weapon in the game that procs (has an effect
that randomly goes off when it is used in combat).&nbsp; Each sword will proc
Ward Summoned an unlimited number of times against summoned mob targets.&nbsp;
Against non-summoned beings, these swords behave like normal swords.&nbsp; If
you're in a zone where you will fight summoned mobs from time to time, you
should give your pet (and all other pets in your group) 2 of these swords.&nbsp;
The effect is the same as your level 12 spell by the same name -- a 35 - 41
point DD vs. summoned.&nbsp; That adds up!</p>

<p><i>Historical Note: This sword used to proc against all targets.&nbsp; Pets
used to proc much more often than players.&nbsp; Together, these two things made
for a very deadly pet.&nbsp; Verant fixed the sword (although it worked the way
it did for nearly a year, it was never intended to work on all targets) and
nerfed pet weapon proc rates at the same time.&nbsp; Essentially, pets now proc
at rates similar to players.</i></p>

<h3>Velium Weapons</h3>
<p>This is a good time to mention velium weapons.&nbsp; Velium weapons drop in
Velious zones.&nbsp; Although you can sell these to NPC vendors for 3 - 5pp
each, you might consider saving a few of them.&nbsp; Velium weapons proc a shard
spell against all targets.&nbsp; The spell doesn't do much damage (around 12
points) but it does add up over the course of an evening.&nbsp; Hand any 2
one-handed velium weapons to your pet to increase its damage output.&nbsp; You
can start hunting in Velious at about level 29.</p>

<h3>Melee</h3>
<p>By now, you should stop using weapons except in the most dire circumstances
(or for fun).&nbsp; You defense should have maxed at level 28.&nbsp; Your
offense should have maxed at level 27.&nbsp; Dodge and weapons skills should
also be at max.</p>
